#. Tag: title
#: introduction.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Введение"

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kxstitch; is a program that lets you create cross stitch patterns and "
"charts. Patterns can be created from scratch on a user defined size of grid, "
"which can be enlarged or reduced in size as your pattern progresses. "
"Alternatively you can import images from many graphics formats. When "
"importing images you can restrict the conversion to full stitches or "
"optionally use fractional stitches. You may also use images as backgrounds "
"resizing them to fit in a selected area. These imported images can then be "
"modified using the supplied tools to produce your final design."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are many tools to aid designing your pattern, from open and filled "
"rectangles and ellipses, filled polygons and lines and backstitching. "
"Additionally cut, copy and paste can be used to duplicate selected areas. "
"Selected areas can also be rotated 90, 180 and 270 degrees anti clockwise, "
"or mirrored horizontally or vertically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is also a pattern library that can be used to store small and not so "
"small portions of patterns that can then be reused in other patterns. The "
"patterns in these libraries are stored in a hierarchical list that makes it "
"easy to sort and navigate them to find the ones you want. These pattern "
"libraries can also be used as alphabets by assigning a character to each "
"one. By using the Alphabet tool, each key press is searched for in the "
"current library and if present, the associated library pattern will be "
"inserted in the pattern."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
